            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Hd1e108">Rubrica 12</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De violentia et coactione</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="3"/>
      ¶ De violentia et coactione. Rubrica. 12.
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e119">
               <lb ed="#V" n="4"/> <ref>MOises in deuteronomio
      <lb ed="#V" n="5"/>c. 24</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e125">Cum repetes
        <lb ed="#V" n="6"/>a proximo tuo rem aliquam: quam de
        <lb ed="#V" n="7" break="no"/>bet tibi: non ingrediaris domum
        <lb ed="#V" n="8"/>eius vt pignus auferas: sed stabis foris: et il
        <lb ed="#V" n="9"/>le tibi proferet quod habuerit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e137">
               <lb ed="#V" n="10"/>
                <ref>¶ Salomon in prouerb. c. 22.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e141">Non facies vio
        <lb ed="#V" n="11" break="no"/>lentiam pauperi: quia pauper est: neque conteres
        <lb ed="#V" n="12"/>egenum in porta: quia dominus iudicabit causam eius.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e150">
               <lb ed="#V" n="13"/>
                <ref>¶ Cronica de nugis philosophorum. c. 6 scilicet de biante:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e154">Bi
        <lb ed="#V" n="14"/>ans vnus de septem sapientibus ait: persuadens
        <lb ed="#V" n="15"/>accipe non violans.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e162">
               <lb ed="#V" n="16"/>
                <ref>¶ Aristoteles rethorn. li. i. c. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e166">Preter naturam
        <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>est violentia.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e172"> <ref>/ 25. c. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e174">Nihil minus coa
        <lb ed="#V" n="18" break="no"/>cti falsa dicunt quam vera: et pertinaces non dicere
        <lb ed="#V" n="19"/>vera: et facile mentientes tanquam requiescitu
        <lb ed="#V" n="20" break="no"/>ri celerius.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e184"> <ref>/ Idem polliticorum libro i. c. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e186">Iustum
        <lb ed="#V" n="21"/>violentum non est.</quote> <ref>/ Li. 5. c. 16.</ref> <quote>Si per frau
        <lb ed="#V" n="22" break="no"/>dem principatur aliquis: vel per violentiam:
        <lb ed="#V" n="23"/>iam hic videtur tyrannus esse. Non volenti
        <lb ed="#V" n="24" break="no"/>bus mox non est rex sed tyrannus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e198"> <ref>/ Idem ethi
        <lb ed="#V" n="25" break="no"/>corum libro 3. c. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e200">Uidetur violentum esse: cuius extrin
        <lb ed="#V" n="26" break="no"/>secus principium est: nihil conferente vim pas
        <lb ed="#V" n="27" break="no"/>so.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e210"> <ref>/ Idem magnorum moralium li. i. c. 17.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e212">Uo
        <lb ed="#V" n="28" break="no"/>luntarium est quod operamur non coacti. Opera
        <lb ed="#V" n="29" break="no"/>tis ex necessitate sequitur tristitia.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e221"> <ref>/ Lib. 2. c.
        <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e223">Tristitia est in his que per coactionem sunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e229">
               <lb ed="#V" n="31"/>
                <ref>¶ Terentius in adelphis:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e233">Que sententia impe
        <lb ed="#V" n="32" break="no"/>rium credat grauius aut stabilius in quod fit: quam
        <lb ed="#V" n="33"/>id quod amicitia adiungitur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e241">
               <lb ed="#V" n="34"/>
                <ref>¶ Ouidius de tristibus lib. 5. emp. 9.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e245">Cedit
        <lb ed="#V" n="35"/>viribus equum. Uitaque pugnaci iura sub en
        <lb ed="#V" n="36" break="no"/>se iacent.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e253"> <ref>/ Epistola. 12.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e255">Adde quod iniustum
        <lb ed="#V" n="37"/>rigido ius dicitur ense.
        <lb ed="#V" n="38"/>Dantur in mediovulnera sepe foro.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e263">
               <lb ed="#V" n="39"/>
                <ref>¶ Quintilianus declam. 5. decla.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e267">Habet pie
        <lb ed="#V" n="40" break="no"/>tas impetum suum: nec vllum dominum nouit effectus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e273">
               <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>
                <ref>/ Declam. 6.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e277">Quicquid in honorem alicuius
        <lb ed="#V" n="42"/>inuentum est: desinet priuilegium vocari posse
        <lb ed="#V" n="43"/>si cogas. Genus seruitutis est coacta libertas</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e286">
               <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>
                <ref>¶ Seneca epistolarum ad lucillum li. 8. c. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e290">Nihil ho
        <lb ed="#V" n="45" break="no"/>nestum est quod ab initio quod a coacta fit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e296"> <ref>/ Idem <!--84.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>de tranquillitate animi:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e298">Male rindent coacta
        <lb ed="#V" n="47"/>ingenia.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e310"> <ref>/ Idem tragediarum introa. c. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e312">Uio
        <lb ed="#V" n="48" break="no"/>lenta nemo imperia continuit diu.</quote> <ref>In octauia
        <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>c. 10.</ref> <quote>Quicquid exprimitur graue est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e320">
               <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>
                <ref>¶ Lex diges. ti. de eo quod metus causa. l. i.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="51"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e324">Uis est maioris rei impetus: qui repelli non
        <lb ed="#V" n="52" break="no"/>potest.</quote> <ref>/ Ti. ad le. acquili. li. scientiam. §. pe.</ref> <quote>Uim
        <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>vi repellere omnes leges omniaque iura permittunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e334">
               <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>
                <ref>/ Ti. de actionibus empti et ve l. si ea res.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e338">Cu
        <lb ed="#V" n="55" break="no"/>stodia aduersus vim parum proficit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e344">
               <lb ed="#V" n="56"/>
               <ref>¶ Macrobius saturnaliorum li. 2. c. 18</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e348">exau
        <lb ed="#V" n="57" break="no"/>tior liberii: Potestas non solum si inuitetur: sed
        <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>et si supplicet cogit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e357">
               <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>
               <ref>¶ Cassiodorus epistolarum li. 2 e. 27.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e361">Nemo co
        <lb ed="#V" n="60" break="no"/>gitur vt credat inuitus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e367"> <ref>/ Lib. 4. e. 10.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e369">Quid
        <lb ed="#V" n="61"/>a bellica confusione pax tranquilla distabit
        <lb ed="#V" n="62"/>si per vim litigia terminentur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e377"> <ref>/ Li. 11. e. 9</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="63"/>  <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e379">Nullus ad violenta confugiat.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e385">
               <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>
               <ref>¶ Claudianus li. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e389">Peragit tranquilla potestas.
        <lb ed="#V" n="65"/>Quod violenta nequit: mandataque fortius vr
        <lb ed="#V" n="66" break="no"/>get Imperiosa quies.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e397">
               <lb ed="#V" n="67"/>
               <ref>¶ Andreas ad gualterium de amore li. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e401">Ma
        <lb ed="#V" n="68" break="no"/>ioribus censetur meritis dignus qui bona spon
        <lb ed="#V" n="69" break="no"/>te pregit quam qui ea coactus exercuerit. Coa
        <lb ed="#V" n="70" break="no"/>cta nemini sunt grata obsequia: et nullis di
        <lb ed="#V" n="71" break="no"/>gna premiis vindicantur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-d1e413">
               <lb ed="#V" n="72"/>
                <ref>¶ Prouerbium vulgar: Forza venze raxone.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="73"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d21956-Qd1e417">La forza e leze cessa.
        <lb ed="#V" n="74"/>El ziga la rana: chi ie mette el pe adosso.</quote>
            </p>
